<!-- ══════════ WEBSITE ANALYSIS ══════════ -->
<div class="page">
  <p class="section-eyebrow">Step 1 — Where You Stand Today</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">Website Analysis:<br>What's Working & What's Missing</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">We reviewed every page of flybeetravels.co.uk to understand the current strengths and the gaps that are costing you leads every single day.</p>

  <div class="analysis-grid">
    <div class="analysis-card good">
      <h4>✓ What's Working Well</h4>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Modern, professional-looking website with a clean design and clear navigation</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Dedicated Umrah package pages (5-night, 7-night, 14-night, Couple Umrah) — good for conversions</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Africa destinations already featured: Cairo, Marrakech, Nairobi, Zanzibar, Cape Town — great foundation</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Contact form and enquiry system in place for lead capture</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Wide range of services: flights, hotels, visa, destinations, Umrah — full travel agency offering</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot green"></span><span>Footer is well-structured with links to all services — helps Google crawl the site</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="analysis-card bad">
      <h4>✗ Critical Problems (Costing You Leads)</h4>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>No blog or content section — Google cannot find you for any search terms</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>Africa destination pages have no individual SEO-optimised landing pages (e.g. no dedicated "Kenya Safari Holiday UK" page)</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>Zero Google visibility — the website is essentially invisible to anyone searching for your services</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>No Google Business Profile optimisation visible — missing local SEO for Middlesbrough</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>No customer reviews or trust signals visible on the website beyond generic testimonials</span></div>
      <div class="analysis-item"><span class="dot red"></span><span>No social media links visible — Umrah community audience cannot find you on Facebook/Instagram</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>The Bottom Line:</strong> Your website looks great but it is like a beautiful shop with no sign above the door and no address on Google Maps. People who are searching for exactly what you offer — Africa holidays from the UK, Umrah packages from Middlesbrough — cannot find you. This strategy fixes that.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ══════════ BUSINESS GOALS ══════════ -->
<div class="page">
  <p class="section-eyebrow">Step 2 — Your Business Goals</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">Two Clear Goals,<br>Two Different Strategies</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">You have two distinct revenue targets, and each needs a different approach. Here's how we tackle both.</p>

  <div class="goal-grid">
    <div class="goal-card seo">
      <span class="goal-icon">🌍</span>
      <h3>Africa Tourism Leads</h3>
      <p>People across the UK are actively searching Google for Africa holiday packages. They type things like "Kenya safari holiday UK" or "Cape Town holiday from UK" and click the first result. Right now, that result is your competitor. SEO puts you there instead.</p>
      <span class="goal-badge">PRIMARY: SEO Strategy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="goal-card social">
      <span class="goal-icon">🕋</span>
      <h3>Umrah Package Bookings</h3>
      <p>Muslims in the UK planning Umrah are not just using Google — they are inside Facebook groups, WhatsApp communities, and Instagram. They trust recommendations from people they follow. Social media puts FlyBee Travels into those trusted circles.</p>
      <span class="goal-badge">PRIMARY: Social Media Strategy</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
